website_summaries.verdict: Add a bit of style to your musical experience with these striking wood headphones.
pros: These headphones wear a lovely rustic look, but they’re quite modern
Sound quality is exceptional with good bass response and strong acoustics
In-line microphone can answer calls, pause music, and activate voice controls
Choose from walnut, maple, or cherry finishes
cons: Noise isolation is passive and only partially filters outside noise

customer_reviews.title: Simple mod for great performance.
customer_reviews.text: Most online reviews are spot on. A bit mid bass heavy/muddy. Overall a nice experience with good staging. Very comfortable. Excellent for use with your phone as they are very efficient. The Mic sounds great. You can also skip the track forward with a double click. Stock sound is as if the highs are hidden behind some veil. It is as if they are accurate but somehow out of reach. They are! Just remove the ear cushions. There is a small piece of foam glued to the plastic in front of the drivers. Simply pull it off. The sound will open up and sparkle. No worries if sibilance or fatigue. Turns the headphones from 3 stars to 4+.
customer_reviews.author: TerryTop Contributor: Photography

customer_reviews.title: Solid quality and good sound
customer_reviews.text: The sound is balanced, with strong but not overpowering or thumpy bass. Several good reviews are available on YouTube.The wiring that goes to both sides may not be everyone's preference, but this design does not require wiring through the headphone body, and allows both sides to receive equal signalling. All material is of very high quality -- I expect these earphones to last. Reasonably comfortable, but I would have liked a slightly bigger earmuff so it is not so close surrounding my ears, and a few mm thicker padding would have been nice.
customer_reviews.author: jkg

customer_reviews.title: I love these headphones
customer_reviews.text: I love these headphones. They have a great sound quality and have worked great thus far in not hurting the cartilage in my ears --which is why I bought them. Although, because there are alot of bots on this product I do need to give an honest review of these because they are not honest in their description. There is no real wood on these headphones. It's plastic with a wood grain detail on it. They are technically 'on the ear' headphones, for someone with large ears. They're not as heavy duty as they look. Very light weight which is a plus for me, but maybe not for everyone.
customer_reviews.author: Chloe Rose

customer_reviews.title: Outstanding for mobiles and laptops
customer_reviews.text: Bought these primarily to use with my mobile, but after 11 months, I'm using them with my laptop at work almost exclusively. Mine are not the most sensitive ears (I'm in my 40's, just glad to hear anything), but I appreciate I can drive these with a cell phone (e.g. while traveling) or a PC without needing a headphone amp. And while my ear is unsophisticated, the phones are delight to wear, as well as behold. They've served me well, and I highly recommend if these are in your price range.
customer_reviews.author: Daniel Isaacs

customer_reviews.title: for 90's hip hop 5 stars, but....3 stars overall.
customer_reviews.text: I am using a Little Dot MKII with a Sanskrit DAC and have sampled several music genres. They only genre that really sounds great is hip hop.....other genres get muddy quickly with suppressed highs and mushy mids at the volume I like. At lower volumes they do sound pretty good. Luckily, I have many other headphones to use for other genres. These are beautiful to look at and seem solid enough, very steampunk-y to me. I got the walnut version. More style over substance but listening to Ministry of Sound's Hip Hop Anthems volumes 1-4 on these are a joy. Not overpowered bass like Beats or the Sony MDR-1A's (EDM monsters) I have, but full lingering thump.
customer_reviews.author: Michael Chumney

customer_reviews.title: They sound great. I have been able to take them to ...
customer_reviews.text: They sound great. I have been able to take them to work for over two years before the wire connection started to loose quality. I believe it lasted this long because I could disconnect the wires. But normal bending has destroyed the current wires. Otherwise the best headset I've had for over five years. I feel that I'm going to get ripped off when ever I go shopping for headsets, and I think the headset market is overrun with crappy headsets. This is a really good sounding, solidly designed midrange headset that's priced midrange.
customer_reviews.author: FurryFriend

customer_reviews.title: Everything but longevity
customer_reviews.text: I LOVE everything about these headphones except longevity. I've had three pairs of these headphones and they each stopped working at about the one year mark. What happens is the Bluetooth somehow stops working. The unit can be charged. It will work in corded mode, but it will stop connecting to my phone and Sonos. Unless you want to purchase a new unit every year I'd stay away from this brand.
customer_reviews.author: 3xlaa2

customer_reviews.title: Great buy for the money
customer_reviews.text: Bought these as part of a 'Lightning deal' for under $40. The good: 1. Sound quality is fantastic for the price. It almost matches the performance of an ATH-M30 that i own.Sound is a little "boxy"; not sure if it's because of the wood or not, but i like it. 2. Great bass response. 3. Physical design is good. The wood definitely makes it look premium The bad: 1. The cords are very flimsy, and they don't tightly couple with the headset. Any movement results in distortions. 2. These should not be called "circumaural". They're more like on-ear headphones; but still pretty comfortable. Not sure if i can wear these for long hours though Overall: Great buy for the money
customer_reviews.author: Funk_it

customer_reviews.title: Crisp, Quality Sound
customer_reviews.text: I must say I wasn't expecting the sound to be so rich, so precise with such clarity. The craftsmanship itself is amazing, real cherry wood and not that press wood. Even the box that it came in was nice, heck I hated to throw it out. If I could borrow from Zenith back in the day, "The quality goes in before the name goes on", Symphonized would be just that, but we all know we can't do that. We don't want Zenith coming after us.
customer_reviews.author: Just A. Customer

customer_reviews.title: False advertising: It is not Over-the-Ear, this style is called: Supra-Aural Headphones.
customer_reviews.text: False advertising: It is not Over-the-Ear, this style is called: Supra-Aural Headphones. These on-the-ear models are designed to perch on the ears rather than to go completely around them. Sound quality was average. Very light weight.
customer_reviews.author: Julia P.

customer_reviews.title: Great looking but...
customer_reviews.text: So first I will say that these are great looking headphones, fit nice & have a decent sound. However, and this is a big however. The headphone cables are so thin that anytime I move my head (thus moving the cable) the sound is transmitted to the headphones. This ruins what otherwise could be a good set of headphones. For little extra cost they could have provided higher quality cables and then really provided something nice. I know this is the company's way of saving few cents.
customer_reviews.author: J. Dieken

customer_reviews.title: Great Headphones, Amazing Customer Service
customer_reviews.text: I've owned a pair of the Symphonized earbuds for over a year and I've been happy with the purchase. So when my 11 y/o son requested headphones for his birthday, I knew where to look. He was thrilled with the look and the Wraith's sound. Unfortunately, being 11, he managed to break the 3.5 mm jack. I contacted Symphonized, hoping I could purchase a new cable. Kara, from Symphonized responded to.my message in less than 24-hours. She then made my day by telling me that Symphonized would send me a cable, free of charge. I didn't even pay postage. Better still, when the package arrived today, they sent 2 cables. How often does a company exceed expectations anymore?
customer_reviews.author: Bobby's Ghost

customer_reviews.title: These headphones sound very good after the initial break-in period
customer_reviews.text: These headphones sound very good after the initial break-in period. I was trying to find a sturdy metal pair of over-ear headphones to use with the PSVR, but these don’t work well for it due to the design of the headband. When using them in VR and looking up, it feels like they can easily fall off. The headband rests on the plastic of the VR headset rather than on my head, which is what causes the problem. Besides the fact that they didn’t fit my reason for getting them, they work great for work and I can wear them all day without issues.
customer_reviews.author: IAmAbe

customer_reviews.title: It's very annoying because I like them in every other way
customer_reviews.text: I would have given this item 4 or 5 stars but after a year of light-normal use the connection between one side of the headphones and the wire leading to the jack became loose and the sound drops out of that side intermittently. It's very annoying because I like them in every other way.
customer_reviews.author: Rachel Globus

customer_reviews.title: they're just beautiful. They're so comfortable to wear too
customer_reviews.text: First of all, they're just beautiful. They're so comfortable to wear too! I love over the ear headphones, but sometimes when I wear my glasses most over the ears are awkward to wear/hurt. Now to the sound: so wonderful. I'm not like a professional music person, but I commute by walking/train and they're perfect. They're much louder than my last pair, listening at half the volume and it's still powerful. I also enjoy that they come with a second pair of cords just in case. I recommend!
customer_reviews.author: Olivia Rondon

customer_reviews.title: Good replacement for Sennheiser HD 461G
customer_reviews.text: My Senneheiser headphones developed a bad chord after 2 1/2 years of moderate use. the chord on those were not replaceable. I searched for headphones with replaceable chords, so hopefully I won't have to replace the whole headset when a chord goes bad. 9-18-18 - Only 1 week in, Sound Quality, Style, and Comfort exceeds the Sennheisers. I was expecting to loose some sound quality or lower comfort due to lower cost, and the "wood finish" I am only a week in, so am unable to speak to durability. I am hopeful. I do like the style as well, but I was hesitant to get these because they seemed too flashy/showy. 5 stars, if I have issues I will update.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Great if you like low frequencies!
customer_reviews.text: I'm using them everyday since few months. I really love them! Great bass signature sound, exactly how I like it (more bass than beats). A little heavy on the head, would not be good for sport activities. When I call with them, the sound is good for the other person. I highly recommend them if you like bass. I listen to a lot of jazz, funk and reggae, where the bass line is important to the groove and symphonized make the music sound great! I also receive compliment about them!
customer_reviews.author: Dimitri

customer_reviews.title: Very happy as this is not my first purchase of a ...
customer_reviews.text: Very happy as this is not my first purchase of a Symphonized product. If you don’t like heavy bass in your music these aren’t the ones for you. I enjoy jazz and R&B and these headphones bring out the deep bass in musical instruments and vocals. When exercising the clear tones of symphonic music spur me on. I don’t need an equalizer just my Symphonized earbuds or my Symphonized headphones. I gave my 14 yo grandson some for Christmas; he told me they’re better than Beats. I need to order another pair b/c now the husband wants some.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Nice headphones.
customer_reviews.text: Nice headphones. Good quality audio when I compare to some other headphones, but nothing amazing if you're an audiophile. Comfortable to use, I wear them at work when I want to drown out the conversations and focus on cranking. They look really nice with the wood detail, and it's also what makes the sound quality.
customer_reviews.author: Lucy

customer_reviews.title: Very good sound for the money. Comfortable.
customer_reviews.text: I can wear these for hours, they sound very good, and provide an open sound that doesn't leave me deaf to what's going on around me. The cable is long and wrapped in a woven fabric that doesn't get caught on things easily. My only complaint is that the hardware has several rivets and joints that catch my long hair and it freaking hurts! I'd buy these again in a heart beat.
customer_reviews.author: Nathan Rogers

customer_reviews.title: Better microphone would make these killer
customer_reviews.text: Only wood style headset that we could really find that works well. Sound is great just wish the microphone could be a bit better.
customer_reviews.author: Marc

customer_reviews.title: Sounds great for less than $100.
customer_reviews.text: The advertisement is confusing. It says "wireless" in the description but says "wired" in the small print. That said, the headphones are worth it. I have pairs of Sennheiser and Sony headphones. I was just curious about the wood panel and whether it makes a difference. I really think it does.
customer_reviews.author: jim

customer_reviews.title: Making music more fun than ever
customer_reviews.text: These headphones really have made listening to music more fun than ever. They are so comfortable and the sound quality is fantastic. My daughter and I did a series of comparisons with several different headphones and these came out first or second place in all of the tests. For the price, the Symphonized headphones seem hard to beat.
customer_reviews.author: Shawn G.

customer_reviews.title: Watch out - not all models are Bluetooth.
customer_reviews.text: I ordered these by mistake (I wanted the Bluetooth ones). They were so comfortable that I returned them and got the ones that I actually wanted. My one complaint is that you have to read carefully to see which ones are and are not Bluetooth. It would be nice if they put the non-bluetooth ones in as a separate item instead of an "option" (like color for a blouse) on the same item.
customer_reviews.author: Digital Goddess

customer_reviews.title: Lightweight and sound great!
customer_reviews.text: The sound was just right for me...bass was good and highs and lows we're just right..only had these few days now but their very comfortable from moment I put them on..the look of the wood is really nice...the only concern I have is the wires are kind of thin but we'll see how they hold up..right now overall I'm happy with my choice of SYMPHONIZED Headphones..
customer_reviews.author: Joseph Carrino

customer_reviews.title: Can't beat them for the money
customer_reviews.text: For the money I can not complain at all. While they are not audiophile quality I would not expect that from the price. However they are quite nice and have very good sound. The finish could be better in my opinion but then again the price is right. Having access to the supplies I will probably refinish then at some point so that they will look even better. As it stands the finish quality makes them look more like plastic than wood. But they re wood, the fit great and sound wonderful.
customer_reviews.author: T.F.Lemieux

customer_reviews.title: Great
customer_reviews.text: Decent physical quality, great sound quality. I have used many pairs of Symphonized headphones, including over-ear, on-ear, ear buds, wireless... All of it sounds great, though the headphones themselves can be flimsy. These over-ear headphones are reliable and have held up for a couple of years.
customer_reviews.author: Chad Klinefelter

customer_reviews.title: After doing the foam-removal mod like others suggested
customer_reviews.text: After doing the foam-removal mod like others suggested, These headphones sound absolutely brilliant. Bass response is nice and clear, but it doesn't feel fake and boosted like beats. Highs are crisp and mids feel warm and filling. The only issue I had with these is that after about 3 hours of continuous use, they tend to make the external part of your ears hurt from the headband tension. I have a somewhat large head, so if you have a smaller head this may not be as much of an issue.
customer_reviews.author: Virginia Safford

customer_reviews.title: Awesome Headphones. Better than Beats
customer_reviews.text: These headphones look great and work great. Comfortable on the ears. I bought them for work because I wanted to shut out distractions. I would say that these headphones block out about 70-80% of normal office noise (people talking, printer noise, foot traffic, etc). I had a pair of Dr. Dre Beats before and will say that my Symphonized Wraith totally beats Beats. The sound quality is about the same. I would argue that the wraith sounds a little clearer than the beats. But it definitely looks way better. The only criticism I have is I wish it came with a nicer carry case than a canvas bag. For the money, get these headphones. You won’t be disappointed.
customer_reviews.author: Pink

customer_reviews.title: The Best Headphones!
customer_reviews.text: I use these headphones everyday whether I'm listening to music on spotify, mixing songs or recording my own stuff. They block out outside noise pretty well and are very comfortable to wear for long periods. I've been using them for at least three years now and they show no sign of wear and tear. Additionally, they look fantastic!
customer_reviews.author: Rachel Burnside

customer_reviews.title: Affordable, High Quality Headphones
customer_reviews.text: I bought these to replace a set of Marley headphones that broke and I'll never go back! These headphones are very well made, comfortable, and sound excellent. They don't seem to put out as much bass as the Marleys did, but the sound is very good and very clear. The only minor "con" that I can see so far is that the inputs for the cable on each ear seem a little bit loose. Hopefully that won't turn into loose wiring and intermittent sound. As a coworker of mine said when he saw them, "These headphones are a work of art!" Highly recommended.
customer_reviews.author: MFerbrache

customer_reviews.title: When I compared with other headphones, this one somehow was the loudest.
customer_reviews.text: I like bass, and when it's gone, it's quite noticeable. I tried 3 different headphones in the same price range and this one is somehow able to reproduce low end frequencies louder than the rest. These don't distort when things get loud.
customer_reviews.author: Anne

customer_reviews.title: Still using them over a year later
customer_reviews.text: I've been using these for over a year, almost two now and they're still going strong. I use them for maybe a hour every day too. My only issue with them is they almost don't adjust to a small enough size for my tiny adult head.
customer_reviews.author: Gem

customer_reviews.title: Great headphones for $39.99!
customer_reviews.text: More base than Sennheiser HD 449, but not as neutral. They also like to "hug" your ears more, making it feel a little tighter, but secluding all the sound straight to your ears. I got these at $39.99 on-sale for gifts. It comes with two cables: one with mic and one without The cable plugs separately into each headphone themselves (left and right) and one to wherever you want sound to come out of. The mic isn't that great, so you're just left with an extra cable instead just in case something happens to the other. They are definitely worth this price and look amazing!
customer_reviews.author: Cruzn1k

customer_reviews.title: Once You Go Wood, You Don't Go Back!
customer_reviews.text: In terms of "fun" or "recreational headphones" (I'm used to studio cans) these are the best in this price range. These wooden cans are drop dead gorgeous in person and I'll often stare at them for a minute before going off to work. And the sound? Second to none. I felt like I was in a movie theater or a concert hall. The bass is deep but with the foam removal mod, the mids and highs shine through without being too harsh.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Defective cord port :(
customer_reviews.text: The headphones arrived immediately out of the box with a loose left cord plugin. Even after hearing the plug snap in securely it wiggles. I tried both cords and it's a problem with the socket. Moving at all makes the left sound cut out. Super disappointing.
customer_reviews.author: NebraskaChick

customer_reviews.title: symphonized Wraith 2.0 just great !
customer_reviews.text: Symphonized Wraith 2.0 , they great head phones well made . I am a mixer engineer and a have many head phones that I use to hear tracks when I'm done mixing a song to hear how the song translate into different head phones . this are great for the prize better then really expensive head phones I own .thanks
customer_reviews.author: Allan j Martinez

customer_reviews.title: Daughter loves them
customer_reviews.text: We were looking for a reasonably priced headset...these turned out to be perfect.
customer_reviews.author: jan tetzlaff

customer_reviews.title: She loves them, just one little problem...
customer_reviews.text: I did a bunch of research and finally decided on these for my teenage daughter. She LOVES them, But.... she just told me that her hair gets caught on the 2 round knobs on each side. (I’m pointing at them in the photo.) She’s a little drama, but said, “I’m getting a bald spot.” 😄
customer_reviews.author: LDS Adventures

customer_reviews.title: ... for 2 years now and I couldn't be more happy with them
customer_reviews.text: I've had these headphones for 2 years now and I couldn't be more happy with them. They have a very rich, full sound (as far as I can tell, not an audiophile), and are very comfortable. I use them at work, and can listen for hours at a time with barely any discomfort. They aren't necessarily noise cancelling, but don't let in much outside sound so that's not really an issue.
customer_reviews.author: minnesota34

customer_reviews.title: An absolute must buy!
customer_reviews.text: Without a doubt, the most accurate natural sound I have ever experienced from a headphone regardless of price. The fact that these headphones are not only gorgeous, but can be had for $50 absolutely staggers the imagination. They easily outperform headphones costing in excess of $300. I am absolutely overwhelmed and amazed. Being a jazz musician, the accuracy of reproduction of individual instruments, voices, full bandwidth clarity and accuracy is top notch.
customer_reviews.author: Jeff

customer_reviews.title: These headphones are amazing. I brought them into work
customer_reviews.text: These headphones are amazing. I brought them into work, and they very much received a lot of compliments. Comfortable to the ears, sound is perfect. I like the level of base. One of the guys from work asked if he could try them on, told me he liked the wood. A reply from the cubical next to me goes, "You like Tim's wood?" Careful if you bring them to work, that's all I'm saying. I bought these at 50% off the original price. So not only did I get premium quality headphones, but at an even better price. Buy these. Take them to work. Watch the comments fly...
customer_reviews.author: DJCally

customer_reviews.title: Okay sound
customer_reviews.text: Packaging - strange Headphones - wooden, good looking and comfortable (dont make ears hot or sweat like the many others) Sound: okay, even with the extra foam (in middle) removed, although the muffled sound goes away, they still sound okay good but not as lively and clear as $15 Panasonic ergonomic bass earbuds
customer_reviews.author: Mverovoy

customer_reviews.title: Great product for the price.
customer_reviews.text: Purchased this for my daughter as a christmas gift and she loves it. It looks like fantastic quality from the outside - great metal and wood with great ear pads. The noise cancellation is not as good as my Bose, but they sound fantastic and do cut out the majority of the outside sound. Great product for the price.
customer_reviews.author: Brian J. Thomas

customer_reviews.title: Symphonized Wraith 2.0 Premium Genuine Cheery Wood
customer_reviews.text: Awesome headphone's very deep bass headphone's the wood make's music sound nicer then plastic headphone's iv had monster's headset's and Sony's and JVC's Turtle beach'es headset's the ELITE 800 and the STEALTH 500P the wood headset's sound's so much better then any of tho's
customer_reviews.author: StealthNCC1701E

customer_reviews.title: I like them so far
customer_reviews.text: Haven't used them much, but the quality of the build is good (i.e. they're not flimsy) and they provide good sound This is my first pair of over-ear headphones and they're comfortable, but I have smaller ears, and also, I've found that if you wear them for an extended period, they can make your ears a little hot (but you have to be wearing them for at least 25-30 minutes before it even becomes noticeable)
customer_reviews.author: JW

customer_reviews.title: Great Headphones.
customer_reviews.text: My wife ordered these for me after I did some research and comparison shopping on the web. I have no doubt I made the right decision. The sound is fantastic with clear pick up on each instrument in back round, voice accommodation and deep base. I would have given 5 stars but fit loosely probably due to my small head. For $60 bucks they a great bargain and would highly recommend for anyone looking to buy over the ear headphones.
customer_reviews.author: NANCY

customer_reviews.title: everything  I expected  it to be
customer_reviews.text: I chose the cherry wood and it's everything I expected it to be the sound quality is amazing comparative all the hits hits that I have in the Turtle Beach headsets I highly recommend this one for some Gamers if you're just wanting audio while you have your Blue Snowball microphone all your stationary microphone bass is really good and it's got amazing sound and I'm glad I bought these because it's hard to find headsets that will fit me I have a really large head and a lot of the plastic microphones will break on me so it's really good quality and a really good build and yes it is real wood
customer_reviews.author: CajunGhostrider

customer_reviews.title: Extremely great bang and boom for your buck!
customer_reviews.text: Great quality and the sound is very nice. Being a Bose, Klipsch, and Beats owner I would have to say for being much cheaper these are audibly better (at least to me ear) in some areas. Will be picking up another pair for my home office very soon. Love them!
customer_reviews.author: James Cribb

customer_reviews.title: Wired Headphones
customer_reviews.text: I bought these for my son for X-mas, I have not tried them. I also bought him the LG V35 and he says they sound great with the 32bit DAC in the LG. He also said he would highly recommend these!
customer_reviews.author: David Mar

customer_reviews.title: Great headphone and wonderful support team.
customer_reviews.text: I don't often leave Reviews on here for product but felt the need to for these guys. Last May, I bought a Wraith after I bought their In-ear headphone. The sound quality for the In-ear one is amazing but I hate having it slip out of my ears. The Wraith itself is the best bargain headphones I've ever bought. My only problem with it was that the cords are not that durable. Mine that has the mic broke recently and I decided to emailed their support to see if they can provide me a new one. With no question asked, they emailed me back saying that a replacement is on the way. That's some really good customer support there.
customer_reviews.author: Ed

customer_reviews.title: Not too bad, good looking
customer_reviews.text: Not too bad, good looking, comfortable, they are on ears headphones rather than full size headphone. The trebles may be muddies because of the foams in front of the drivers. There is a lot of sub-bass, and bass, mid bass is a little overwhelmed. Some trebles is showing. All in all is a good value for the price, but nothing special. If you love bass and boom with some what trebles.
customer_reviews.author: Whitigir

customer_reviews.title: Nice but flimsy
customer_reviews.text: I love the look of these and the sound is good. But they are flimsy. They don't hold on your head tight. I can hear when someone else wears them, what they're listening to. My kid nearly snapped them in half.
customer_reviews.author: KT

customer_reviews.title: Might not be a good buy for those with larger than average head, or ears
customer_reviews.text: Might not be a good buy for those with larger than average head, or ears. There is a high possibility that the outer contour of your ears will be in direct contact of the lining/grill of the inside of the headphone.
customer_reviews.author: Owen

customer_reviews.title: Great Sound, Unique Appearance
customer_reviews.text: Bought 2 pair, in different wood tones, for my two sons; One son is an adult, the other a teenager; both love the sound and the unique appearance of wood inserts; I would buy again on appearance alone, but they assure me the sound is great.
customer_reviews.author: Dr. Jeff Shearer

customer_reviews.title: Nice headphones, good sound
customer_reviews.text: Nice headphones, good sound. I had a pair of Panasonic RP-HTX7-R1 headphones that I loved so these have big shoes to fill, but so far so good. I have long hair so it sometimes gets snagged in the metal components. It comes with a little pouch but no case. Looks great but I do feel like I can't toss them around and have to be careful I don't smoosh them in my bag because they seem a little fragile.
customer_reviews.author: Topaz

customer_reviews.title: Overall - pretty good for the price
customer_reviews.text: Nice set of headphones. Sound quality is good. Looks good. Not sure how well they will hold up. Unfortunately a mix of high quality components (stainless and wood) and low quality components (plastic, chromed plastic, fake leather). The synthetic leather on the headband (glued on) and on the ear pieces looks / feels cheap and I expect it to crack and fail in a few years.
customer_reviews.author: Bob Fraundorf

customer_reviews.title: These headphones were working fine for about 3 months and then the signal became ...
customer_reviews.text: These headphones were working fine for about 3 months and then the signal became glitchy every time I moved the connection cord. I am unable to receive clear sound as it intermittently gets interrupted with even the slightest move of the connection wire. I should be able to exchange them but alas the policy has now closed. It is completely unacceptable.
customer_reviews.author: Lyuba Dutchak

customer_reviews.title: Great Product
customer_reviews.text: These have very warm and natural sound, maybe the best I've ever heard from a pair of headphones. They were shipped promptly and were packaged nicely. I'm so glad I took a chance on these.
customer_reviews.author: K. Johnston

customer_reviews.title: Volume Control
customer_reviews.text: Volume controlled stopped working after a couple months. The sound a great, but I am disappointed the volume control no longer works. I would not risk purchasing this product again.
customer_reviews.author: R. Maywald

customer_reviews.title: The audio is pretty good (burn it in a little with loud music ...
customer_reviews.text: The audio is pretty good (burn it in a little with loud music for an hour or so). Clear highs, moderate lows. Super comfy ear pads, but the metal headband can probably pull hair if your hair is really long. I had no hair issues, though my hair is short. Only issue is a really short cable, so if you're looking to hook this up to a desktop PC, make sure you have an extension or an easy access to the headphone port.
customer_reviews.author: Jyang

customer_reviews.title: Bang for your buck
customer_reviews.text: Noise cancellation is great, sound quality is really good. I gave 3 stars for volume control, only because it's actually very loud when its connected to my PC, so I keep the volume on my PC around 15/100 and that is plenty loud enough. Theres also the scratching that comes along when the wire rubs something the wrong way, but thats expected of any wired headset. For the price, you probably wont find anything better. Highly recommended.

customer_reviews.title: Solid Pair of Headphones

The headphones are also comfortable for my cranium, even after several hours of wear. Though they don't have noise-cancelling tech, the over-ear construction dampens background noise reasonably well. While I am no audiophile, these headphones exceeded my expectations - good sound quality, comfortable design, sturdy construction, pleasing aesthetics, and a reasonable price.
